OREON Fan Maintenance Manual

Scope: cooling tower fans, forced draft fans, induced draft fans, and ventilation units.

Normal operation: vibration below 4.5 mm/s RMS, noise below 88 dB, stable current, clean blades,
secure foundation bolts, and unobstructed airflow.

Fan imbalance indicators include high vibration, increasing noise, blade deposits, erosion, damaged
blades, missing balance weights, loose hub, or resonance after speed changes. Corrective actions:
stop fan if vibration exceeds trip level, clean blades, inspect blade pitch and cracks, tighten
foundation bolts, and perform dynamic balancing.

Cooling performance degradation may come from fouled fill media, poor airflow, motor overload, or
blocked intake screens.
